Please get the Word Out that Jodi Purdy is looking for 3 Generations from Rhode Island - Grampa, his Son and his Grandson for a Commercial for a Medical Company.  

This pays $500 per person for one day on set with a professional crew and award-winning Director.

I just cast 16 actors in one of my clients Commercials in Austin Texas! Surely, I can find 3 in Rhode Island!

The boy has to live in Rhode Island.  So a boy between 6 and 9 and his dad would be great! I can find an actor to play the Grampa!!

Familiar Faces Casting Call Short Fim Directed by: Daniela Aguirre DATE POSTED: 09-22-2025 POSSIBLE SHOOTING DATES: November 8th OR November 9th, 2025 Rehearsal dates: TBD Location: Chicago, IL
We are committed to diverse, inclusive casting. For every role, please submit qualifiec performers, without regard to disability, race, age, color, national origin, ethnic origin, sexua orientation, gender identity, or any other basis prohibited by law unless otherwise specifically indicated.
Logline : A college undergrad soaring to become a pediatric speech therapist is taunted by ar unexplainable nightmare that has gradually become worse over time.
Roles:
Katalina Desdemona (22) ( Portrayed female Lead) - A senior year college undergrad who grew up in an abusive houschold that impacted her by severely delaying her speech development. With ome help from her ELD teacher (English Language Development) Katalina was able to express herself more growing up and dreams of doing the same for others,
Young Katalina (7-9) (Portrayed female- lead)- Evil spirit who imitates the appearance o Katalina when she was younger. Who's seeking to collect her promised teeth.
Pierre Baker (22) (Portrayed male- supporting)- The loyal best friend of Katalina since 5" grade and who also took interest in studying for child development and literacy. Dedicated and nurturing best friend
If interested, available, or have questions email Daniela Aguirre Send headshots, resumes/reels 

to email: daguirre2@colum.edu

Deadline Date: October 24th. 2025
Compensation: Meal, Copy, Credit

Please note current height, weight, clothing and shoe sizes*

Are you comfortable around atmospheric smoke?

If 21+, are you comfortable smoking a herbal cigarette, if asked? (It‚Äôs ok if not)

Men: Are you comfortable being clean shaven for the shoot if needed?

Men & women: Are you comfortable receiving a 1960‚Äôs haircut on set, if needed?

Are you local to NJ/NY area?

Confirm you are 18 years or older

Attach current, clear photos (close-up and full body)

This background role is not covered by SAG-AFTRA CBA and subject to a preference of employment provision.

items.title: K√∏benhavns film- og fotoskole s√∏ger kvindelig skuespiller til midtvejsproduktion (overbygning)!

items.text:
S√òGER AKUT SKUESPILLER, KVINDE 65+ 

Grundet sygdom er vores skuespiller i morgen desv√¶rre hoppet fra, s√• vi s√∏ger akut en Kvinde p√• 65+ der kunne have lyst til at v√¶re med. Projektet er desv√¶rre ul√∏nnet, men der er forplejning og god stemning p√• set. 

Lokation: Spring forbi strandpark 
Tidsrum: Dagstimerne
‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî
Tidligere opslag: 

Vi er et ungt hold af filmskabere, som s√∏ger en kvindelig skuespiller, der kunne have lyst til at arbejde sammen med os et par dage, n√•r vi optager vores kortfilm ‚ÄúEventyret om Fr√∏prinsen‚Äù d. 19-21. og 26-28. September. Rollen er ikke l√∏nnet da det er et lidt mindre projekt, som er finansieret ud af egen lomme.

Historien:

Et moderne og f√∏lsomt ungdomseventyr om 12-√•rige Matilde, en ensom pige med store dr√∏mme om √¶gte k√¶rlighed. En dag ser hun en dreng gennem en h√¶k, som idyllisk sidder og skriver i sin have. Noget ved ham fanger hende. Mathilde bygger en smuk fantasi op omkring ham, som hun bliver besat af.

Hun m√• i kontakt med ham. Men det er ikke let, n√•r fantasien og virkeligheden skal m√∏des, slet ikke n√•r drengens bedstemor, som han bor hos, ikke ligefrem er typen der tror p√• k√¶rlighed ved f√∏rste blik.

En smuk og melankolsk fort√¶lling om l√¶ngsel, dr√∏mme og den f√∏rste k√¶rlighed. Et twist p√• det klassiske fr√∏prins eventyr.

Bedstemoderen:

Sigrid repr√¶senterer et mere pragmatisk syn p√• k√¶rlighed og giver ikke meget for den medrivende forelskelse, som Matilde v√¶gter s√• h√∏jt. Hun finder den upassende og derfor er hun ikke interesseret i, at de to unge mennesker skal m√∏des

items.title: S√òGER AKUT SKUESPILLER, KVINDE 65+

items.text:
Hej allesammen

Vi er et par elever fra KBH Film- og Fotoskole, der er i gang med vores midtvejs projekt. 

Vi har skrevet en ca. 12-min lang kortfilm, hvori en ung mand ikke n√•r sit S-tog fra K√∏ge Nord st, fordi han bliver blokeret af en hund. I den forbindelse vil vi h√∏re, om der er nogen som kunne have lyst til at l√•ne deres vuffer (og dem selv) til nogle unge ambiti√∏se filmskabere i ca. 1 time. 

Vi leder efter en mellemstor hund -- race er underordnet. Den skal helst kunne finde ud af at holde fokus p√• et enkelt menneske, sitte, og kunne hoppe op ad en person. 

Hvor og hvorn√•r?

Vi filmer allerede tirsdag d. 30 september kl. 19-20. Optagelserne foreg√•r p√• K√∏ge Nord st. Vi d√¶kker for forplejninger p√• set, og transport

Vigtig info
* I den endeligt klippet film vil det fremg√•, at hunden bliver skubbet af en person. Dette er et stunt vi naturligvis vil skabe udelukkende med kameratricks, og hunden vil ikke rent faktisk blive skubbet
* Vi vil selvf√∏lgelig gerne have ejeren med p√• set, s√• hunden f√∏ler sig tryggest

Hvis dig og din hund kunne v√¶re interesseret, s√• skriv en privat besked, eller en mail til vores instrukt√∏r Dizzie p√• dizzie.saugmann@gmail.com, med kontakt info, et vellignende billede af vovseren, og gerne lidt om dens personlighed.

P√• foreh√•nd tak!

## Dramatic Improv Workshops from Theatre Momentum! We're proud to present:
# **Get in Focus - An Online Subversive's Workshop** with David Razowsky
# Sundays, October 5-26 ¬∑ 12-3 PM Central

What are you focused on when you begin a scene? What great offers are you missing because you‚Äôre building a story instead of connecting to your emotional responses? This four-week online workshop will teach you how to use the power of kinesthetic responses to immediately build strong scenes, recognize what your body is already telling you, and then build a great connection from there.

This is an excellent primer for those who‚Äôve never studied with Dave.

**Sundays, October 5-26, 12-3 PM Central [VIA ZOOM]**

https://www.theatremomentum.com/guest-classes

items.text:
Hello, Nice to meet you. 

I'm Yoshikazu Saito, a Tokyo-based actor currently producing a film. And for this project, I'd like to show the story of a man born in japan and adopted in United States. It is Japanese cinema but, to challenge norms, in Japanglish. I mean in Japanese-English.

Currently, we need more financial support to develop the film. With your donate of our film, we could continue with our concept, showing that we have our ways of owning universal languages.

Below is a link to our PayPal, open for your support for our vision. And please share the proposal with your friends. 

Our team will also appreciate if you will share it with your friends as well.

Thank you very much and I wish you have a great day.
 

Donate via PayPal.Me
https://paypal.me/tvt2010?locale.x=ja_JP&country.x=JP

Welcome to our Warsaw Impact Community!

We‚Äôre growing fast, and we‚Äôre excited to have you here. Whether you‚Äôre a passionate crowd member, an art lover who wants to connect with the artists you see on stage, or a creative looking to network, this is your place.

If you‚Äôre an aspiring artist thinking about how to earn money from your craft and take the leap into becoming a full-time creative, you‚Äôll find support, ideas, and inspiration here. This community is all about connection, creativity, and growth.

Together we learn, share, and improve as artists through exclusive workshops, meetups, live shows, festivals, and more, crucially, we‚Äôre building a space where the right people can discover you. Actors, musicians, and performers in our community are regularly seen by casting agents, talent scouts, and industry professionals who come to our events looking for fresh talent. If you want exposure, meaningful industry connections, and a real chance to be discovered, this is the place to be.

We‚Äôre glad you‚Äôve joined us, get ready to perform, connect, and be seen.

üåê impactwarsaw.com

Telegram group: https://t.me/+BGl_Q7Qg5wI4NTY0

Instagram: @impactfestwarsaw

items.text:
Tickets are now available for our upcoming Actors and Filmmakers Networking Event, taking place on Sunday, October 26th.

 

Networking is essential for advancing your career in the industry, and Marble Academy for Drama and Management has proudly facilitated these events for years. With over 90 attendees, our June gathering was a tremendous success, and we are determined to build on that momentum.

 

You will have the opportunity to engage with accomplished actors, visionary directors, prominent producers, and skilled crew members who can offer valuable insights and possibly help bring your next project to life.

 

Think about it, if there were an event where you could connect with exceptionally talented cast and crew who could help bring your next project to life, wouldn‚Äôt you want to be there?

 

Take a look at this video from a previous event‚Ä¶..

www.youtube.com/watch?v=EM4jwjRxny4

 

So, join us on Sunday, October 26th, from 2 PM to 6:30 PM at HOME Mcr, located at 2 Tony Wilson Place, Manchester, M15 4FN.

 

Secure your tickets through this link:

www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/actors-and-filmmakers-networking-event-tickets-1509159349239

 

I look forward to seeing you there!

items.text:
CASTING CALL

We‚Äôre looking for a female actor to join us this December for our RAPUNZEL pantomime (school tour). 

We‚Äôre casting either of the following parts, with our existing performer playing the opposite role. 

- Rapunzel (lead)
- Gothel (villain)

Last year was our best selling tour - but we hope to beat that this year! Because it‚Äôs schools, the shows are weekday mornings and early afternoons, so you‚Äôll have your evenings and weekends free. The performances are in the Norfolk, Suffolk and Cambridge area. 

We‚Äôre currently offering a minimum of ¬£870 - which will go up as we get more bookings in + travel expenses. 
The tour spans from 1st - 19th December 2025. 
Aiming to start weekly rehearsals asap - in Hunstanton (PE36). These are unpaid but we keep them as flexible as possible.

This will be our thirteenth panto tour, and we‚Äôve built up a good name in the area, with schools booking us year after year (even before we announce the title!) We pride ourselves on being a warm, friendly, but professional company.

If interested, please get in touch for further details - either by a PM on here, or via email - purple-dreams@hotmail.co.uk - I‚Äôm looking forward to hearing from (some of) you üôÇ

Many thanks
Tobias Nicholls
Creative Director 
Purple Dreams Productions

INTENSE CRIME DRAMA - SHORT (PAID)

1-day shoot in London (UK) for 2nd week in October 2025 (date tbc)

(For actors based in the London area).

 

Summary: A night of heavy drinking ends in a deadly contest between newfound besties - a fearless Nigerian gangland enforcer and a trigger-happy European gunman.

 

This project is Episode #0 of ‚ÄòBrave Hunter in Ghost City‚Äô  - introducing a new African story world and some of its main characters. ** **

 

MALE LEAD: to play fearless gangland enforcer.  Black African, 25-45, Lagos accent, 5‚Äô6‚Äù+, athletic physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

MALE LEAD: to play trigger-happy gunman. White European,  35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 85kg-100kg,  powerful physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

SUPPORTING MALE: to play dead gangster. White European, 35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 80kg-100kg. Half a day of shooting for ¬£150 for 7 hours.

 

You will need professional experience playing character roles on Stage, Film or TV. Please send in a cover letter, your CV with headshot and your showreel to Davina Brown at k2Filmworks@gmail.com

items.text:
The first 10 mins of my first full length play Blackout 1985 is going to be performed as part of Wooden Arrow Productions next scratch evening on 30th October at Lamda at their Sainsburys Theatre!

The casting is UNPAID but there will be professional photography, industry guests for feedback and a chance to network after with the guests and the audience. There are also other roles in other plays that need filling. 

Deadline is this Saturday!

Synopsis of Blackout 1985: 28th September 1985. A day marked in history. The Lewis family gathers in their living room as the streets outside erupt in flames. Winston and Angie strive to protect their children, Jimmy and Asha, from a world that denies their humanity. As generational wounds, dreams, and tensions collide, the family must decide whether to stay safe behind closed doors or step into the fire of history. Blackout 1985 is the first in the trilogy, which shines a light on key Black British moments.

If you are interested or know anyone please go to this link - 
https://forms.gle/uJFMiQzyR6kVqBae8

items.text:
Hello folks, my Film And Video Production students decided to begin a very ambitious project - Feature Film! Those of you who work in the industry already know how much time, effort and money it take to do a good movie, for those of you who don't know I can tell you - a lot! If you like to help them on their journey, please take a time to read their message below and if you decide to help them, please follow the link to their GoFundMe page. I've seen them in action and I've read the script, this project worth to be filmed!                                                                                                                                         

What happens when film students try to wrangle Greek Gods on a student budget?

Hey Calgary film fam, 

We're a group of SAIT film students in our final semester, and we've taken on our biggest project yet : Prometheion - a student-led feature film inspired by Greek mythology, with a bonus BTS to show the beautiful chaos making it. 

We're pouring in long day and nights, all our are creativity, and yes... way too much craft table pizza. But to really bring this story to life, we could use some extra support for wardrobe, props, locations, and keeping our crew alive through it all. 

Here's our GoFundMe : https://www.gofundme.com/f/prometheion-student-feature-film?attribution_id=sl:0597d4f7-f1e5-4ff2-86ce-2da6a9373dd2&lang=en_CA&ts=1758595706 

 Every bit helps us make this film with the ambition it deserves, and we'd be so grateful if you can contribute or share. 

 Thanks for helping us light the fire of Prometheion!

items.text:
Hi Everyone!

I'm a student studying filmmaking at **Birmingham City University**, and for one of our assignments, we are creating a **short film** and are looking for actors.

The concept isn't decided yet, but we are deciding between two:
1. A past chess champion reminisces about his glory days and replays the match that he lost in which started his downfall.
2. A girl whose inner self is screaming at her to help, while she is sucked into her phone, a film themed on how addicted we are to our phones.

We have a Test Shoot Day on the 23rd of October, 9:00am-12:00pm, and the Shoot Day is on the 4th of November, 9:00am-4:00pm. Both are at Parkside Building, Birmingham City University.

As we are students, this will be unpaid, unfortunately. But this is a great opportunity for actors who are starting out and want to get something on their resumes. We will include you in the credits.

We will have more details before the shoot, so don't worry.

If you are interested, please send an email to this address: **maisie.condron@mail.bcu.ac.uk**

Please include this information:

- Name

- Age

- Sex

- Location

- A self-tape of any performance

We will also be having more films come up in the future, so if you don't fit any of the roles described, you can still send an application in!

Thank you!

sharedPost.text:
The Foundry Acting Studio

Where Professional Training Meets Real Opportunity

At The Foundry Acting Studio, we believe every actor deserves a world class education without barriers, hidden costs, or false promises.

Our curriculum‚Ä¶. built and refined over six years,  is internationally recognised, exceeding Spotlight‚Äôs accreditation requirements by more than three times. We are Spotlight approved, SAG recognised, and currently in talks with other major organisations worldwide. Our work is supported by acclaimed writers, directors, and actors connected to some of the most influential platforms in the industry.

What makes us different:
 ‚Ä¢ World Class Curriculum: Designed to equal the top schools in the world, yet offered at a fraction of the cost.
 ‚Ä¢ No Hidden Tiers or Costs: Every actor receives the same training. There are no ‚Äúhigher levels,‚Äù upsells, or paywalls. Your talent is never defined by your wallet.
 ‚Ä¢ Personal Coaching: We keep classes small, so every actor is seen, heard, and individually assessed with hands on guidance.
 ‚Ä¢ No Agency Agenda: We are not an agency. You will never pay us for a promise of representation. Our focus is training and opportunity, not commission.
 ‚Ä¢ Industry Films: We are the only UK studio guaranteeing work by producing industry standard films with RED and ARRI cameras‚Ä¶. work that goes directly on your Spotlight profile.
 ‚Ä¢ Equality & Integrity

At The Foundry Acting Studio, we believe in building the industry, not dividing it. For that reason, we do not accept students who are currently in the middle of a paid term with another school or who are tied to an agency that is directly run by that same school. We respect the work of fellow coaches and do not believe in poaching actors away from their commitments.

Once an actor has completed their term elsewhere and is no longer represented under an agency attached to another school, they are welcome to join us for a fresh start. This ensures absolute fairness, integrity, and clarity for everyone involved.

Because The Foundry is not an agency, your place with us is never tied to representation. When you train here, your development is entirely about your craft. If you do not currently have an agent, our team will guide you toward finding one that best suits your path, independent, professional representation that has nothing to do with paying for classes.

We believe this creates a healthier, more transparent industry for all‚Ä¶ actors, coaches, and agencies alike.

 ‚Ä¢ Accessibility: Whether you are working full-time, on benefits, retired, or just beginning your journey, our training is affordable and inclusive. Discounts are available for civil servants.
 ‚Ä¢ Expanding Opportunities: Teen classes are launching soon, and new locations are opening across the UK.

Our Philosophy

When you walk through our doors, you are not a number, not a ‚Äúpound sign,‚Äù and never a currency. You are an actor, with equal right to professional training, opportunity, and growth.

At The Foundry, we believe in community. We believe in supporting fellow actors, fellow coaches, headshot photographers, showreel specialists, fight choreographers, and everyone who contributes to the craft. Together, we build the industry.

Ready to Join?

Direct message us today for full details on class times, dates, and locations near you. Step into a studio that is reshaping the future of acting in the UK and beyond.

The Foundry Acting Studio
Professional. Inclusive. Respected. Recognised

items.text:
**CASTING CALL TIL KORTFILM P√Ö KBHFF **

Hej alle,

Vi s√∏ger 3 skuespillere til et midtvejsprojekt "Noget for Nogen" p√• K√∏benhavns Film og Foto skole. 

"Noget for Nogen" er et trekantsdrama sat inden for rammerne af en romantisk horror. Et k√¶restepar lader en fremmed kvinde overnatte i deres nye hus, men fra f√∏rste √∏jeblik bliver parret spillet ud mod hinanden, alt imens aftenen tager en mere og mere okkult drejning. Overlever parforholdet til en ny dag?

**ROLLER:**

**SOSJA** (20'erne - 30'erne) - HOVEDKARAKTER

Sosjas st√∏rste √∏nske at v√¶re mor og k√¶mper for at f√• sin k√¶reste til at dele hendes dr√∏m. Hun finder stor mening i at v√¶re noget for nogen. 

**JAKE** (20'erne - 30'erne) - Sosjas k√¶reste

Har et stort behov for at finde sig selv og sin hylde i livet. Han er arbejdsl√∏s og lyver om at v√¶re steril, for at undg√• at f√• b√∏rn. 

**LUCY** (20'erne - 30'erne) - Den fremmede g√¶st

Vil gerne friste og manipulere Sosja og Jakes forhold, for at se hvor langt hun kan presse dem og i sidste ende √∏del√¶gge deres forhold. Hun er en repr√¶sentation af dj√¶velen og det okkulte element. 

Skriv en PB eller send en mail til nogetfornogenfilm@gmail.com, hvis det v√¶kker interesse

Vi h√•ber I vil v√¶re med, og vi gl√¶der os til at h√∏re fra jer!

Bh,

William, Mathias, Marius og Benjamin

**KALDER ALLE STATISTER ‚Äì KBH film og fotoskole s√∏ger statister***** *****til***** ny kortfilm *****‚ÄúT√∏brud‚Äù, *****der handler om brud, fortid og uventede m√∏der:***

Vi s√∏ger 8-10 unge statister fra 16 til 22 √•r til en festscene, der foreg√•r i en lejlighed i K√∏benhavn. 

Det eneste det kr√¶ver er, at du er im√∏dekommende og er klar p√• at v√¶re med til at skabe en ambiti√∏s film. 

**HANDLING:**

**‚ÄúT√∏brud‚Äù skildrer m√∏det mellem to verdener ‚Äì **en midaldrende kvinde, Malene skal underskrive sine skilsmissepapirer, men bliver forstyrret da overboen, en 15 √•rig dreng holder fest. Hun g√•r op for at klage, men det viser sig ikke at v√¶re s√• simpelt, og det udvikler sig til en skandal√∏s aften, hvor Malene konfronteres med sin egen fortid. 

**PRAKTISK INFORMATION**

**Optagelser foreg√•r i K√∏benhavn fra 3.okt til 4.okt**

**UL√òNNET, men vi s√∏rger for forplejning og god stemning!**

**Hvis opslaget har v√¶kket interesse?**

**Send et CV til ****[mushagedorn@gmail.com](mailto:mushagedorn@gmail.com)**** senest 1.oktober.**

**CASTING CALL ‚Äì KBH film og fotoskole s√∏ger skuespillere til *****en ny kortfilm *****‚ÄúT√∏brud‚Äù, *****der handler om brud, fortid og uventede m√∏der:***

**HANDLING:**

**‚ÄúT√∏brud‚Äù skildrer m√∏det mellem to verdener ‚Äì **en midaldrende kvinde, Malene skal underskrive sine skilsmissepapirer, men bliver forstyrret da overboen, en 15 √•rig dreng holder fest. Hun g√•r op for at klage, men det viser sig ikke at v√¶re s√• simpelt, og det udvikler sig til en skandal√∏s aften, hvor Malene konfronteres med sin egen fortid. 

**Malene (35-50 √•r)**

Malene er en kvinde undervejs til en skilsmisse. Hun fors√∏ger at holde sig oven vande, men i virkeligheden er hun p√• kanten til et sammenbrud og har endnu ikke accepteret sin nye virkelighed. Hun savner fortiden og finder noget genkendeligt i Ludvig den unge overbo.

**Ludvig den unge overbo (16-20 √•r)**

Overboen, der holder fest. Gr√¶nses√∏gende, overlegen og en anelse provokerende. Leger med Malene.

**Eksmand (35-50 √•r)**

Eksmand til Malene. Irritabel og ivrig efter at f√• skilsmissen overst√•et.

**En ung pige (16-20 √•r)**

Uskyldig, mystisk, konfronterer Malene med sin tilstedev√¶relse.

**PRAKTISK INFORMATION**

**Optagelser foreg√•r i K√∏benhavn fra 3.okt til 5.okt**

**Ul√∏nnet, men vi s√∏rger for forplejning og god stemning!**

**Hvis opslaget har v√¶kket interesse?**

**Send en kort pr√¶sentationsvideo og CV til ****gracjanklemczak.pl@gmail.com**** senest 1.oktober.**

üé¨ **EXTRAS NEEDED ‚Äì SHORT FILM (GLASGOW)** üé¨
**LADY MACBETH WAS NEVER A GIRL**
Location: Glasgow | Filming: 18‚Äì19 October 2025 | Unpaid (snacks provided)

We‚Äôre casting **extras aged 18+** to play **15‚Äì16-year-old students** in a **1990s British secondary school, **for a short queer coming-of-age drama.

This is a **collaborative, unpaid project** ‚Äî ideal for emerging actors, students, or anyone curious about being on a film set and helping create something intimate and atmospheric.

**We‚Äôre especially keen to hear from male-identifying individuals** who enjoy playing **football (casually or recreationally)** ‚Äî there will be background scenes involving schoolyard football.

* No acting experience needed ‚Äî just the right look and energy.
* It‚Äôs a period piece, so natural styles preferred (no visible tattoos/piercings, 90s-appropriate looks).
* You‚Äôll be helping us bring to life the textured, emotionally charged world of 90s school life.

**TO APPLY:**
Please email **francesca.mcbride@outlook.com** with:
* Your name + age
* A recent photo
* Confirmation that you are available on 18‚Äì19th Oct
* A few lines about yourself ‚Äî feel free to mention if you play football!

üí¨ Tag or share with anyone who might be up for this.
Let‚Äôs make something quiet, searching, and beautifully defiant.

*Some things don‚Äôt belong in lost property...*

#GlasgowFilm #ShortFilmCasting #ExtrasCall #StudentFilm #QueerCinema #ScottishFilm #FootballExtras #CastingCall #LadyMacbethWasNeverAGirl

items.text:
The first 10 mins of my first full length play Blackout 1985 is going to be performed as part of Wooden Arrow Productions next scratch evening on 30th October at Lamda at their Sainsburys Theatre!

The casting is UNPAID but there will be professional photography, industry guests for feedback and a chance to network after with the guests and the audience. There are also other roles in other plays that need filling. 

Deadline is this Saturday!

Synopsis of Blackout 1985: 28th September 1985. A day marked in history. The Lewis family gathers in their living room as the streets outside erupt in flames. Winston and Angie strive to protect their children, Jimmy and Asha, from a world that denies their humanity. As generational wounds, dreams, and tensions collide, the family must decide whether to stay safe behind closed doors or step into the fire of history. Blackout 1985 is the first in the trilogy, which shines a light on key Black British moments.

If you are interested or know anyone please go to this link - https://forms.gle/uJFMiQzyR6kVqBae8

Vagabond Pictures

sharedPost.text:
Vagabond Pictures is a film production company devoted to telling stories that travel‚Äîacross borders, boundaries, and the human soul.
Rooted in tradition but always in motion, we follow the story wherever it leads‚Äîinto forgotten corners, overlooked lives, and the quiet moments that shape our world. From the windswept coasts to the back alleys of cities steeped in history, our films explore identity, conflict, belonging, and truth.
We believe in the power of cinema not just to entertain, but to connect‚Äîto move hearts, shift minds, and honour voices often left unheard. Whether it's documentary or fiction, every project begins with a deep respect for craft, culture, and character.
We are filmmakers, yes‚Äîbut first, we are wanderers. And we‚Äôre here to capture the world as it truly is. One story at a time.

Join us TODAY for the 12th Annual Empowerment Weekend, an educational theatre event dedicated to empowering and advancing the careers of solo theatre performers. This weekend promises a rich lineup of workshops and panels led by industry experts, specifically designed to elevate the skills and career trajectories of solo artists, while also providing information relevant to any type of performer.

Participants will gain invaluable insights into creating and marketing a solo show, mastering teamwork, refining touring strategies, and honing career development skills. With a selection of 8 dynamic workshops and panels, including an exclusive interview with the Co-Founder of LAWTF, attendees are poised for a weekend of growth and networking.

Tuition for the weekend is $125 General Admission, or $75 per day. 2for1 Buddy passes available for both the weekend or one day and students PWYC!

Workshops will take place at Theatre 68 in North Hollywood.

Founded in 1993 by Adilah Barnes and Miriam Reed, the Los Angeles Women‚Äôs Theatre Festival holds the distinction of being the oldest Annual Solo Festival in Los Angeles celebrating powerful women performers. A critically-acclaimed international festival, LAWTF has produced close to 700 extraordinary solo artists from around the globe. These multicultural and multi-disciplined performers represent diverse disciplines as theatre, dance, storytelling, performance art, performance poetry, spoken word, mime, music and song.

All in all, this is the most information you will find about the production of solo performance at one time in one place. Come out, support and enjoy!

https://www.eventbrite.com/e/lawtfs-2025-empowerment-weekend-tickets-1596462003829

Please submit resume, headshot, and demo reel (if applicable) to       Onlyforadaysf@gmail.com                  and indicate which role you‚Äôd like to be considered for. The selected actors will be sent sides with self-tape instructions.

Logline
A lonely Korean girl meets a magician hired to play her father for one day. A lie that becomes the most magical memory of her childhood.

Genre
Family Drama

Tone & Keywords
Warm, gently magical, grounded realism, themes of memory, identity, belonging, immigrant family, quiet humor.

ROLES
1) YUNSEUL / Ïú§Ïä¨ (Lead)
Female, 5-12, Korean. Sensitive, curious, and quietly lonely after moving to Canada. Hair‚Äëtwisting habit reveals anxiety. a believer who finds wonder in small things. The emotional heart of the film.
Language: English (primary), Korean (bonus).
Guardian: Parent/guardian required.

2) MAGICIAN (Lead)
Male, 25‚Äì35, Korean/Korean American. Witty on the surface, quietly lonely underneath. hides wounds behind jokes and tricks. A father‚Äëfor‚Äëa‚Äëday who is changed by Yunseul‚Äôs trust.
Language: English (primary), Korean (bonus).
Notes: Open to learning simple magic.

3) JUNGHEE / Ï†ïÌù¨ (Lead)
Female, 25‚Äì35, Korean/Korean‚Äëdescent. Protective, practical, and loving; carries guilt over the story she tells her daughter about the absent father. Hires the Magician out of fierce love and hope.
Language: English (primary), Korean (bonus).

4) CHUY (Supporting)
Male, 25‚Äì35, Korean/Korean‚Äëdescent. Playful ‚Äúuncle‚Äù energy, eases the mood with quick humor. Quietly honest protects the boundary of magic so it keeps its power.
Language: English (primary).

items.text:
Hey everyone my name is Manraj Heer I‚Äôm the producer for our student short film at Vancouver Film School. The film is called ‚ÄúBeginnings‚Äù and we are shooting on October 11th & 12th, 2025. We are currently looking to hire three male actors. For the roles of Athan, Hooded Man, and Rick. If you are interested please send your resume, headshot, and any demo reel to teambeginnings@gmail.com and we will reach out to you for a self tape to help narrow down the process.

The deadline for demo tapes and applications end on October 3rd, 2025. So please get in your application at your earliest convenience.

Synopsis:
Athan celebrates his 21st birthday surrounded by the people he loves the most. Family and
friends cheer for the start of a new phase of Athan‚Äôs life. A new beginning. Until time suddenly
stops. Everyone freezing in place, except for Athan, who knows the memory has ended.
Guided by a Hooded Man, an older and wiser version of himself, Athan must find purpose by
visiting rooms in a seemingly never-ending hallway, each filled with crucial moments of his life
‚Äî learning the role of the people that surround him (and the impact he has on them), dealing
with love in an ever-transforming relationship, and embracing grief from the never-stopping
passage of time.
After impulsively deciding to skip entering the rest of the doors out of agony, Athan will find
how quickly a lifetime goes by ‚Äî but be ready to accept his new chapter behind a final, bright room.

CASTING BREAKDOWN ‚Äì VANCOUVER FILM SCHOOL
Project Title: Beginnings
Project Type: Student Short Film
Union Status: Non-Union
Director: J. D. Estevez
Producer: Raj Heer / Vancouver Film School
Casting Director: Manraj Heer, J. D. Estevez
Audition Dates: Self-tapes due by October 3rd, 2025
Audition Location: Self-tapes only
Call Back Dates: October 4th, 2025
Call Back Location: 142 Water Street, Vancouver, BC V6B 1B2
Shooting Dates: October 11th ‚Äì 12th, 2025
Shooting Location: Greater Vancouver Area
Rates: Unpaid. Catering and craft service provided.
Submission Instructions: Please submit resume, headshot, and demo reel
to teambeginnings@gmail.com and indicate which role you‚Äôd like to be considered for.

ATHAN / MALE / AGE : 20-25 / ANY ETHNICITY 

Na√Øve and foolish, Athan thinks he knows what he wants from life and what it is to be expected of him ‚Äî learning soon enough that you can never be prepared for what is behind
the next door. Though he is slow to realize the importance of every moment, and too clumsy
to show it, Athan is a deeply caring and empathetic person. He is willing to push everything
out of his way to spend more time with someone he loves. Despite repeatedly stumbling
through the hallway of life, Athan is motivated by a constant search for meaning.

HOODED MAN / MALE / AGE : 50-60 / ANY ETHNICITY
After living as a rebellious young Athan, the Hooded Man walks through the hallway of his life
once again. This time, he reflects on his past, accepting it for what it is, knowing he cannot
change it. Melancholic and somewhat regretful, he guides Athan, emphasizing the
importance of embracing every stage of life, whether joyful or somber. Unlike his younger
self, the Hooded Man moves deliberately through every memory, without hurry, but with
peace. Though seemingly stoic, there is a hint of disturbance behind his expression.

RICK / MALE / AGE : 40-50 / ANY ETHNICITY
Athan‚Äôs father, Rick, is a troubled man. He learned from his family to hide his true feelings and
often relies on bad habits to forget his past mistakes. He was able to distance himself from his
vices when he found a sense of purpose, such as when he married his childhood friend,
Emma. However, it didn't last long. Overwhelmed by regret and fearing that he won‚Äôt make
the most of his life, Rick sees Athan as a chance to start over. He is determined to ensure that
his son won't make the same mistakes he did. However, with his marriage falling apart and
Athan soon becoming independent, Rick can‚Äôt help but start drinking again.

 Look forward to seeing everyone‚Äôs submissions! If you have any questions or concerns please reach me at teambeginnings@gmail.com.

The centre has a number of displays showing the vast historical significance of the area. 

The show was in aid of Sheppey 92.2Fm Community Radio. 

Sat night we shall be in Boughton Monchelsea, Maidstone!

items.text:
**PROJECT NAME**: *DESTINATION OSHAWA*

**PROJECT TYPE:** *WEBSERIES - COMEDY*

**STATUS:*** NON-UNION*

**COMPENSATION**: DAILY HONORARIUM *CAD $2*00/Day- please note cast and crew for this project are working on an equity daily honorarium. 

**SYPNOPSIS**:  [Hannah is suddenly appointed director of the Oshawa Tourism Board due to her boss‚Äôs unexpected passing. She is tasked with getting Oshawa off the ‚ÄúWorst Cities in Canada‚Äù list by the end of the year. With almost no resources or time, it‚Äôs up to Hannah to inspire her chaotic team and fulfill her promise of putting Oshawa on the map (in a good way).](https://www.canva.com/design/DAGYFsS-yL4/PVPHv0y53k9FrFZNwakJOg/view?utm_content=DAGYFsS-yL4&utm_campaign=designshare&utm_medium=link&utm_source=editor#page-1)

***SHOOTING LOCATIONS:**** Richmond Hill + Oshawa*

***PRODUCTION DATES: ****October 17-24 (individual shoot dates TBD)*

***CASTING SUBMISSION INSTRUCTIONS: ***

*To request an audition and sides, please send headshots, reels and any info to **[casting@combobravo.com](mailto:casting@combobravo.com)** with the character name in the subject line. ****ie - BELLA RANDAZZO - ASHLEY***

***CHARACTER****:  *Ashley
***Role Type****: *Lead

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ****33*

***Episode: ****1-4*

***Appearance: ****Brown Hair, sweet face. *Neat, tidy, formal wear in the office. Patagonia vests, khakis on field trips. *Think Gabe Lewis (The Office)*

***About Character:**** *Liaison to City Council, Ashley has always been passionate about efficient government bureaucracy to a fault. His do-gooder nature has always made him generally unlikeable by his peers and higher ups. In high school he was the first class president to be impeached by faculty, and he was the first student to ever be assassinated at model UN. Despite that he never lost his innocence, and kept on pursuing his dream of joining the Canadian government. He loves his job as Council Liaison and self-appointed apprentice to Bill Tuft. He planned his life out long ago and it is going exactly according to plan, until he met Hannah. He fell in love with her as soon as she started working as Bill‚Äôs assistant, and when he was drafted to join the Tourism Task Force, he dedicated himself to making sure her goals are achieved. She is truly the one person in his life that throws his rational, ordered nature into disarray. 

***CHARACTER****:  *Sarah

***Role Type****: *Lead

***Presenting Gender: ***Woman

***Age: ****20*

***Episode: ****1-4*

***Appearance: ****5‚Äô2, petite, unassuming student. *

***About Character:**** *Newest intern at Oshawa City Hall. Was reassigned to the Tourism Task Force. In a constant state of panic. She wants to please everyone all the time but is constantly second guessing herself. She is very introverted unless she‚Äôs having one of her stress- induced, fugue-state outbursts. Fearing for the other students safety, Sarah was sent to Oshawa City Hall by her guidance counsellor as they felt a ‚Äúnoncompetitive and ineffectual environment‚Äù would be a good change of pace for her. The task force team is unfazed by her outbursts and for the first time Sarah feels as though she‚Äôs found her pack. Their acceptance helps Sarah gain confidence and start standing up for herself.

***CHARACTER****:  *Deborah

***Role Type****: *Lead

***Presenting Gender: ***Woman

***Age: ****60*

***Episode: ****1-4*

***Appearance: ***Stocky, older, greying a bit but also dyes her hair. Business casual, but stopped updating her wardrobe in the 90s.

***About Character:**** *Has been working at City Hall since gaining her business degree from Durham College. She stopped caring about her job around the time everything moved online and although she would never admit it, feels a bit archaic and forgotten. She‚Äôs annoyed she was moved onto Hannah‚Äôs task force as she doesn't want to waste her time learning new skills for a project that seems destined to fail. She‚Äôs not bitter, she's just seen it all before. Eventually, Deborah is motivated after some emotional vulnerability from Hannah, perhaps remembering a younger version of herself.

***CHARACTER****:  *Bill Tuft

***Role Type****: *Reoccuring

***Presenting Gender: ***Man

***Age: ****51*

***Episode: ****1-2, 4*

***Appearance: ***Tall, athletic, greying. Suit with no tie kind of guy, but always a flashy pocket square. On fridays and weekends he wears his golf attire. Think Richard Greenwood, (Workin‚Äô Moms)

***About Character:**** *Former real estate agent, but has been the Ward 5 City Councillor 15 years running. Bill is considered a ‚ÄúGreybeard‚Äù or municipal government. He‚Äôs been at it for a long time and knows all the ins and outs. He‚Äôs incredibly popular, not just because of his extreme charisma, but also his moral flexibility when it comes allowing a ‚Äúhealthy dose‚Äù of political corruption. **STATUS:*** NON-UNION*

She is tasked with getting Oshawa off the ‚ÄúWorst Cities in Canada‚Äù list by the end of the year. With almost no resources or time, it‚Äôs up to Hannah to inspire her chaotic team and fulfill her promise of putting Oshawa on the map (in a good way).](https://www.canva.com/design/DAGYFsS-yL4/PVPHv0y53k9FrFZNwakJOg/view?utm_content=DAGYFsS-yL4&utm_campaign=designshare&utm_medium=link&utm_source=editor#page-1)

His do-gooder nature has always made him generally unlikeable by his peers and higher ups. In high school he was the first class president to be impeached by faculty, and he was the first student to ever be assassinated at model UN. Despite that he never lost his innocence, and kept on pursuing his dream of joining the Canadian government. He loves his job as Council Liaison and self-appointed apprentice to Bill Tuft. He planned his life out long ago and it is going exactly according to plan, until he met Hannah. He fell in love with her as soon as she started working as Bill‚Äôs assistant, and when he was drafted to join the Tourism Task Force, he dedicated himself to making sure her goals are achieved. She is truly the one person in his life that throws his rational, ordered nature into disarray.

***Episode: ****1-4*

items.text:
Rainhill Garrick Society are performing ‚Äò Habeus Corpus‚Äô by Alan Bennett on February 12th-14th 2026.

Alan Bennett‚Äôs Habeus Corpus is set some time in the Seventies and follows the lives of the Wicksteed family. The story follows Dr and Muriel Wicksteed as they both seek pleasure and fun outside of their marital relationship. The farcical play is very fast paced, incredibly funny and occasionally surreal. The bumbling sex-obsessed British characters such as the virginal vicar, the Ô¨Çat chested spinster, the peering doctor, his frustrated wife and of course a bra salesman man all come together in this bizarre and thoroughly entertaining story.

Parts available:-

Dennis Wicksteed - the hypochondriac son of Dr Wickseed, (20-30)

Felicity Rumpers - young, nubile, upper class  (20-30)

Constance Wicksteed - the sister of Dr Wicksteed, flat chested and sex starved, (20+) 

Play read through Tuesday 21st October at 7.30 in Rainhill Village Hall
Auditions- Thursday 23rd October at 7.30 Rainhill Village Hall 
Rehearsals are on Tuesdays and Thursday evenings 7.30-9.30 and the 3 Sundays prior to the performance.
Audition pieces are available on request. 

We are an amateur group so the roles are unpaid, but we are a well respected group of 83 years standing who enjoy great support from a large dedicated audience. 
The play is great fun with some slapstick and music but with some poignant moments that say a lot about relationships.

For further information contact: sophiebrogan99@gmail.com
